Today Sen Klobuchar met w/officals & held a press conference @mspairport about @TSA staffing cuts. Klobuchar has sent two letters since last fall to TSA Administrator Pekoske urging the agency to increase staffing at MSP to address increases in wait times at security checkpoints. pic.twitter.com/0YaQymm9VK

This is one of the reasons I previously wrote to TSA Administrator David Pekoske urging him to increase staffing at MSP to address recent increases in wait times at checkpoints, and why I am renewing my call for TSA to act.-AK https://www.klobuchar.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/news-releases?ID=E8C18D9B-6AEE-43AA-A258-7AAEA7095298 …
It is critical that officials do everything possible to mitigate the impact on wait times caused by this construction, particularly as MSP has seen the numbers of passengers at the airport increase.

It is simply unacceptable that TSA staffing at @mspairport has decreased while passenger traffic has increased. http://www.startribune.com/long-tsa-checkpoint-lines-try-patience-of-msp-travelers/553909732/ …
